        "taskDescription": " <strong>Goal: </strong>Read the information given by your instructor. Construct a model for a 20 year old man who weighs 180 pounds, is 71 inches tall, and is moderately active (HB Factor = 1.55). Show his weight change if he consumes 500 less calories than he burns each day. After constructing the model click \"Show Graph\" or \"Show Table\" to enter your own values. Then complete the worksheet. <strong>BMR Formulas </strong>(weight is in pounds, height in inches, age in years): Women: BMR = 655 + (4.35 x weight) + (4.7 x height) - (4.7 x age) Men: BMR = 66 + (6.23 x weight) + (12.7 x height) - (6.8 x age) <strong>Harris Benedict Formulas: </strong> Sedentary (little or no exercise): BMR x 1.2 Lightly active (light exercise/sports 1-3 days/week): BMR x 1.375 Moderately active (moderate exercise/sports 3-5 days/week): BMR x 1.55 Very active (hard exercise/sports 6-7 days a week): BMR x 1.725 Extra active (very hard exercise/sports): BMR x 1.9 ",
